headline: JPMorgan Accuses Charlie Javice of More Fraud. This Time Over Her Legal Bills.
summary: JPMorgan Chase  says it has been cheated by  Charlie Javice  yet again.  On Friday, the biggest bank in America asked a Delaware judge to reverse an order requiring it to front the legal bills for Javice, the entrepreneur who was convicted of defrauding the bank in March.  JPMorgan  bought Javice’s startup, Frank, in the summer of 2021 for $175 million.

headline: Progressive Stock Got Hit After Earnings. It’s Time to Buy One of America’s Great Companies.
summary: Progressive  is one of America’s great financial companies, with a phenomenal record of growth and stock market performance since its 1971 IPO.  Progressive, the No. 2 U.S. auto insurer, is a financial growth stock and, unfortunately, growth has been slowing in recent months.  Auto insurance prices increased by double digits in 2023 and 2024, but Friday’s September consumer-price report showed a 0.3% decline in auto insurance premiums.

headline: Exclusive: Elizabeth Warren Warns Banks Against Lending $20 Billion to Argentina
summary: Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D., Mass.) told the biggest banks in the country not to finance a $20 billion loan to Argentina, citing the financial risk the facility would pose both to depositors and U.S. taxpayers.  Warren sent letters to JPMorgan Chase, Bank of America, Citigroup and Goldman Sachs saying that a $20 billion loan to President Javier Milei’s government “would raise serious safety and soundness concerns…given the shaky creditworthiness of Argentina and its apparent lack of valuable collateral.”  The banks have been seeking details from the Treasury Department on how they can be sure they will get their funds back, The Wall Street Journal reported.
